A time bomb was found in a department store visited  by Prince Charles, heir to the British throne, during his recent visit to  Saint Petersburg, Moscow television said Saturday in a report monitored in  London.
The television said security guards found a bomb on May 16 in the  Littlewoods store on Saint Petersburg's Tukhachevsky Avenue.
The four-kilogram TNT device was discovered by security guards in a  plastic bag. A timer connected to the detonator was set to go off at 08:00  hours.
"Had the explosive device gone off, the shop would have been blown to  pieces. The Prince of Wales did visit Littlewoods but at another time,"  according to the television report monitored by the BBC.
Prince Charles was in Saint Petersburg from May 16 to 19 and visited  Littlewoods on the 18th.
